    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600 Models
        Built Before 05/20/2003 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - BACK-UP LIGHTS - EXTENDED DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXTENDED DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>Refer to the
            <hotlnk document="s082503_152.xml" xrefid="f0826002">Back-Up Lights Connector Diagram</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>When the transmission is shifted into reverse, transmission circuits will apply battery voltage to backup
            lamp/turn signal splice (4810) and the back-up lights.
        </para>
        <para>Ground for the back-up lights is supplied from ground stud (4006) to stop tail &#38; turn connector (9303)
            terminal E.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
